def parse(x):
    return datetime.strptime(x,"%m/%d/%Y")

ASSUMPTION OF MOVING AVERAGE :¶

  1. Time series is stationary
  2. it has a very slow varying mean or constant mean ............... if your Data lot of fluctuations & if your data non-stationary mean then may be MA might be the not best model for forecasting

Here my data aset is not stationary , just show you various moving averages react to it . beacuse if i take a stationary data , then all the moving average might look similar . so i'm goinng to take non stationary data, and showing you how it's perfom non stationary data.

Simple Moving Average¶

Simple Moving Average =(t+(t-1)+(t-2)+...+(t-n))/n

here i'm takking n=3 . i.e, window=3

Weighted Moving Average¶

Weighted Moving Average=(tweighting factor)+((t-1)weighting factor-1)+...+((t-n)*weighting factor-n)/n

In [30]:
def w_MA(weights):
    def calc(x):
        return (weights*x).mean()
    return calc

Exponential Moving average =(close -previous EMA)*(2/(span+1))+previous EMA
